content.description:
A steep crank with excellent edges over a bad landing. This problem is unnamed and rated 10d in the Fry guide.

Shown to me many years ago by a very fit old-timer.

Start on the right arete of the narrow and high south face of first large boulder on the right as you descend from the top of the Island.
content.location:
Head south from the top of the

Island

, trending to the west, toward the road. Look for a tall boulder on your right. This problem ascends the right arete of the high and narrow south face of this boulder.

Also, it is located to the right of

Her Crack

and the old aid seam.

content.description: Rated B1 in the So Cal Bouldering guide. Â I tried it a few times but never got it.
A good hard mantle. Tiptoe up the steep slab as high as you can, reach for the sloping top, fight your way over.
content.location: On the steep and featureless section of the wall, left of center.

content.description: Scamble onto the initial slab to reach holds the lead over the bulge to alligator skin consisting of coarse knobs and flakes. Take care with the hollow sounding cap block/flake at the top.
content.location: Seven feet left (west) of Her Crack.

content.description:
Slightly overhanging bombay chimney. An excellent grovel.

Squeeze up the chimney, trying to avoid the boulder on the left. Exit up a short hand crack until you are on top of a flake. Climb the short slab to the top for extra excitement.

10c in the Fry guide.
content.location:
Head south from the top of the

Island

, trending to the west, toward the road. Look for a tall boulder on your right. Turn right just south of this boulder and into a small alcove.

To the left of

Problem A

and the aid seam.
